where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: You can tell me what this is.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Well, whattaya know. I ain't seen one of these since I was prospecting on Subterrel beyond the Outer Rim!
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Do you know where it came from ?
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: This baby belongs to them cloners. What you got here is a Kamino Kyberdart.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Kamino Kyberdart I wonder why it didn't show up in any analysis archive.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: It's these funny little cuts on the side give it away Those analysis droids you've got over there only focus on symbols, you know. I should think you Jedi would have more respect for the difference between knowledge and wisdom.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Well, Dex, if droids could think, we wouldn't be here, would we? Kamino doesn't sound familiar. Is it part of the Republic?
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: No, it's beyond the Outer Rim. I'd say about twelve parsecs outside the Rishi Maze, toward the south. It should be easy to find, even for those droids in your archive to find. Those Kaminoans keep to themselves. They're cloners. Damned good ones, too.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Cloners? Are they friendly?
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: It depends.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: On what, Dex?
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: On how good your manners are and how big your pocketbook is.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, DEX'S DINER - MORNING

text: Did you call for assistance?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: Yes yes, I did
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: Are you having a problem, Master Kenobi?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: Yes, I'm trying to find a planet system called Kamino. It doesn't seem to show upon any of the archive charts.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: Kamino? It's not a system I'M familiar with Let me see. Are you sure you have the right co-ordinates?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: According to my information, it should be in this quadrant somewhere just south of the Rishi Maze.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: It ought to be. Unless it was very recent. I hate to say it, but it looks like the system you're searching for doesn't exist. That's impossible perhaps the archives are incomplete.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: If an item does not appear in our records, it does not exist!
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, ARCHIVES LIBRARY - DAY

text: It must be difficult having sworn your life to the Jedi not being able to visit the places you like or do the things you like
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: Or be with the people I love.
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: Are you allowed to love? I thought that was forbidden for a Jedi.
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: Attachment is forbidden. Possession is forbidden. Compassion, which I would define as unconditional love, is central to a Jedi's life, so you might say we're encouraged to love.
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: You have changed so much
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: You haven't changed a bit. You're exactly the way I remember you in my dreams. I doubt if Naboo has changed much either.
where: INT. STARFREIGHTER, STORAGE HOLD - DAY

text: Don't think feel be as one with the Force. Help you, it will. Younglings - enough! A visitor we have. Welcome him.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Master Obi-Wan Kenobi, meet the mighty Bear Clan.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Welcome, Master Obi-Wan!
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: I am sorry to disturb you, Master.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: What help to you, can I be?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: I’m looking for a planet described to me by an old friend. I trust him. But the system doesn’t show up on the archive maps.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: An interesting puzzle. Gather round the map reader, younglings. Master Obi-Wan has lost a planet. How embarrassing. How embarrassing! Liam, the shades. Gather round the map reader. Clear your minds and find Obi-Wan's wayward planet we will.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: This is where it ought to be but it isn’t. Gravity is pulling all the stars in this area inward to this spot. There should be a star here but there isn’t.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Most interesting. Gravity’s silhouette remains, but the star and all its planets have disappeared. How can this be?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Because someone erased it from the archive memory.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Truly wonderful, the mind of a child is. Uncluttered. To the centre of the pull of gravity go, and find your planet you will. The data must have been erased.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: But Master Yoda who could have erased information from the archives? That’s impossible, isn’t it?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: Dangerous and disturbing this puzzle is. Only a Jedi could have erased those files. But who and why, harder to answer. Meditate on this I will.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, TRAINING VERANDA - DAY

text: I wasn't the youngest queen ever elected but now that I think back on it, I'm not sure I was old enough. I'm not sure I was ready.
where: EXT. NABOO PALACE, GRAND COURTYARD (NABOO) - AFTERNOON

text: The people you served thought you did a good job. I heard they tried to amend the Constitution so you could stay in office.
where: EXT. NABOO PALACE, GRAND COURTYARD (NABOO) - AFTERNOON

text: Truthfully, I was relieved when my two terms were up. The new Queen asked me to serve as Senator, I couldn't refuse her.
where: EXT. NABOO PALACE, GRAND COURTYARD (NABOO) - AFTERNOON

text: I agree! I think the Republic needs you I'm glad you chose to serve.
where: EXT. NABOO PALACE, GRAND COURTYARD (NABOO) - AFTERNOON

text: If the senate votes to create an army, it's sure to push us into a civil war.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: It's unthinkable! There hasn't been a full-scale war since the formation of the Republic.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Do you see any way, through negotiations, to bring the separatists back into the Republic?
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Not if they feel threatened. The separatists don't have an army, but if they are provoked, they will move to defend themselves. I'm sure of that. And with no time or money to build an army, my guess is they will turn to the Commerce Guilds or the Trade Federation for help.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: It's outrageous! After all of those hearings, and the four trials in the Supreme Court, NUTE is still the Viceroy of the Trade Federation. Do those money mongers control everything?
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: We must keep our faith in the Republic. The day we stop believing democracy can work is the day we lose it.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Let's pray that day never comes.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: In the meantime, we must consider your own safety.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: What is your suggestion, Master Jedi?
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Anakin's not a Jedi yet, Counsellor. He's still a Padawan learner. I was thinking
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Hey, hold on a minute!
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Excuse me! I was thinking I would stay in the Lake Country. There are some places up there that are very isolated.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Excuse me? I am in charge of security here, milady.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Ani, my life is at risk, and this is my home. I know it very well that is why we're here. I think it would be wise for you to take advantage of my knowledge in this instance.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Sorry, milady.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Perfect. It's settled then.
where: INT. NABOO PALACE, THRONE ROOM - AFTERNOON

text: Master Jedi, The Prime Minister expects you.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR ENTRANCE

text: I'm expected?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR ENTRANCE

text: Of course! He is anxious to see you. After all these years, we were beginning to think you weren't coming. Now please, this way!
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR ENTRANCE

text: May I present Lama Su, Prime Minister of Kamino and this is Master Jedi
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Obi-Wan Kenobi.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Please, I trust you are going to enjoy your stay. We are most happy you have arrived at the best part of the season. And now to business. You will be delighted to hear we are on schedule. Two hundred thousand units are ready, with another million well on the way.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: That is good news.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Please tell your Master Sifo-Dyas that we have every confidence his order will be met on time and in full. He is well, I hope?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: I'm sorry Master - ?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas. He's still a leading member of the Jedi Council, is he not?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Master Sifo-Dyas was killed almost ten years ago.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: I'm so sorry to hear that. But I'm sure he would have been proud of the army we've built for him.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: The army ?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Yes, a clone army, and I must say one of the finest we've ever created.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Tell me, Prime Minister when my master first contacted you about the army did he say who it was for?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: Of course he did. This army is for the Republic. But you must be anxious to inspect the units for yourself.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: That's why I'm here.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, PRIME MINISTER OFFICE - DAY

text: When I was in Level Three, we used to come here for school retreat. See that island? We used to swim there every day. I love the water. We used to lie on the sand and let the sun dry us and try to guess the names of the birds singing.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, GARDEN TERRACEM LATE AFTERNOON

text: I don’t like sand. It’s coarse and rough and irritating, and it gets everywhere. Not like here. Here everything’s soft and smooth.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, GARDEN TERRACEM LATE AFTERNOON

text: I shouldn't have done that.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, GARDEN TERRACEM LATE AFTERNOON

text: I'm sorry.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, GARDEN TERRACEM LATE AFTERNOON

text: Very impressive.
where: EXT. TIPOCA CITY, PARADE GROUND (RAINSTORM) - DAY

text: I'd hoped you would be pleased.
where: EXT. TIPOCA CITY, PARADE GROUND (RAINSTORM) - DAY

text: Clones can think creatively. You will find that they are immensely superior to droids. We take great pride in our combat education and training programs. This group was created about five years ago.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: You mentioned growth acceleration.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: Oh, yes, it's essential. Otherwise, a mature clone would take a lifetime to grow. Now we can do it in half the time.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: I see.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: We modified their genetic structure to make them less independent than the original host. As a result they are totally obedient, taking any order without question.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: Who was the original host?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: A bounty hunter called Jango Fett.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: Where is this bounty hunter now?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: Oh, we keep him here. After a few hundred thousand clones, the genetic pattern starts to fade, so we take a fresh supply. He lives here, but he's free to come and go as he pleases.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, COMMINSSARY - DAY

text: Apart from his pay, which is considerable, Fett demanded only one thing - an unaltered clone for himself. Curious is not it?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: Unaltered?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: Pure genetic replication. No tampering with the structure to make it more docile and no growth acceleration
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: I would like to meet this Jango Fett.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: I would be most happy to arrange it, for you.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: Magnificent, aren't they?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CLONE CENTER, BARRACKS - DAY

text: I don't know
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Sure you do you just don't want to tell me.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Are you going to use one of your Jedi mind tricks on me?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: They only work on the weak-minded.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: All right his name was Palo. I was twelve. We were both in the Legislative Youth Program. He was a few years older then I very cute dark curly hair dreamy eyes.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: All right, I get the picture whatever happened to him?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: I went on to become a Queen. He went on to become an artist.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Maybe he was the smart one.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: You really don't like politicians, do you?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: I like two or three, but I'm not really sure about one of them. I don't think the system works.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: How would you have it work?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: We need a system where the politicians sit down and discuss the problems, agree what's in the best interests of all the people, and then do it.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: That is exactly what we do. The trouble is that people don't wlways agree. In fact, they hardly ever do.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Then they should be made to.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: By whom? Who's going to make them?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: I don't know. Someone.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: You?
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Of course not me.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: But someone.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Someone wise.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: That sounds an awful lot like a dictatorship to me.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Well, if it works
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: You're making fun of me.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Oh no, I'd be much too frightened to tease a Senator.
where: EXT. NABOO, MOUNTAIN MEADOW - LATER AFTERNOON

text: Boba, is your father here? May we see him?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR - DAY

text: Sure.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR - DAY

text: Dad! Taun We's here!
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Welcome back, Jango. Was your trip productive?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Fairly.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: This is Jedi Master, OBI-WAN Kenobi. He's come to check on our progress.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Your clones are very impressive. You must be very proud.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: I'm just a simple man, trying to make my way in the universe, Master Jedi.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Ever made your way as far into the interior as Coruscant?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Once or twice.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Recently?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Possibly
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Then you must know Master Sifo-Dyas?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Boba, close the door.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Master who?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Sifo-Dyas. Isn’t he the Jedi who hired you for this job?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Never heard of him. I was recuited by a man called Darth Tyranus on one of the moons of Bogden.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: No? I thought
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Do you like your army?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: It seems to me it's your army - being that they are all clones of you.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: They'll do their job well, I'll guarantee that.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: I look forward to seeing them in action. Thank you for your time, Jango.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Always a pleasure to meet a Jedi.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: What is it, Dad?
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: Pack your things. We're leaving.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, FETT APARTMENT - DAY

text: And when I got to them, we went into aggressive negotiations.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, EAT - TWILIGHT

text: "Aggressive negotiations"? What's that?
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, EAT - TWILIGHT

text: Well, negotiations with a lightsaber. If Master Obi-Wan caught me doing this, he'd be very grumpy.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, EAT - TWILIGHT

text: From the moment I met you, all those years ago, a day hasn't gone by when I haven't thought of you. And now that I'm close to you again, I'm in agony. The closer I get to you, the worse it gets. The thought of not being with you mskes my stomach turn over - my mouth goes dry. I feel dizzy. I can't breathe. I'm haunted by the kiss you should never have given me. My heart is beating, hoping that kiss will not become a scar. You are in my very soul, tormenting me. What can I do? I will do anything you ask. If you are suffering as much as I am, tell me.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: I can't. We can't. It's just not possible.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: Anything's possible. Padme, please listen
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: You listen. We live in a real world. Come back to it. You're studying to become a Jedi Knight. I'm a Senator. If you follow your thoughts through to conclusion, they will take us to a place we cannot go regardless of the way we feel about each other.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: Then you do feel something! That is something I know I cannot do. Believe me, I wish that I could just wish away my feelings but I can't.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: I am not going to give into this.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: It wouldn't have to be that way we could keep it a secret.
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: Then we'd be living a lie - one we couldn't keep even if we wanted to. I couldn't do that. Could you, Anakin? Could you live like that?
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: No, you're right. It would destroy us
where: INT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, FIREPLACE ALCOVE - TWILIGHT

text: Tell your Council the first battalions are ready. And remind them that if they need more troops, we will need time to grow them.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR - DAY

text: I won't forget. Thank you.
where: INT. TIPOCA CITY, CORRIDOR - DAY

text: I have successfully made contact with the prime minister of Kamino. They are using a bounty hunter named Jango Fett to create a clone army. I have a strong feeling that this bounty hunter is the assassin we are looking for.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Do you think these cloners are involved in the plot to assassinate Senator Amidala?
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: No, Master. There appears to be no motive.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Do not assume anything, Obi-Wan. Clear your mind must be if you are to discover the real villains behind this plot.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Yes, Master. They say Master Sifo-Dyas placed an order for a clone army at the request of the senate almost ten years ago. I was under the impression he was killed before that. Did the council ever authorize the creation of a clone army?
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: No. Whoever placed that order did not have the authorization of the Jedi Council.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Bring him here. Question him we will.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Yes, Master. I will report back when I have him.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Blind we are if creation of this clone army we could not see.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: I think it is time we informed the senate that our ability to use the Force has diminished.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Only the dark lord of the Sith knows of our weakness. If informed the senate is multiply our adversaries will.
where: EXT. JEDI TEMPLE, LIVINF QUARTERS - EARLY EVENING

text: Don't go.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

text: I don't want to disturb you.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

text: Your presence is soothing.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

text: You had a nightmare again last night.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

text: Jedi don't have nightmares.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

text: I heard you.
where: EXT. NABOO LAKE RETREAT, LODGE, BALCONY OVERLOOKING GARDENS - MORNING

where: INT. GEONOSIS, CONTROL - DAY

text: There are too many.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, CONTROL - DAY

text: This is not looking good at all!
where: INT. GEONOSIS, CONTROL - DAY

text: We must get the starships back into space.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, CONTROL - DAY

text: My master will never allow the Republic to get away with this treachery. I will take the designs with me to Coruscant. They will be much safer there with my master.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, CONTROL - DAY

text: Hold on! Look over there
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: It's Dooku, go after him! Padme!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: We're gonna need some help!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: There isn't time! Anakin and I can handle this!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: Put the ship down! Down!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: No! Forget her. We have to go after Dooku.
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: Follow that speeder!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: No we're not! Land this ship!
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: Don't let your personal feelings get in the way. We've got a job to do.
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: I don't care! Go back.
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: I can't take Dooku alone! I need you! If we catch him, we can end this war right now! We have a job to do! What do you think Padmé would do were she in your position?
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: She would do her duty.
where: INT. GUNSHIP NUMBER TWO - DAY

text: You'll pay for all the Jedi you've killed today, Dooku.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: We'll take him together.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: I'm taking him now!
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: No, Anakin! No!
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Kenobi, isn't it? As you can see, my Jedi powers are far beyond yours. Now, back down.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: I don't think so.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Grand Master Kenobi, you disappoint me. Yoda holds you in such high esteem.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: That's brave of you, boy - but foolish. I would have thought you'd have learnt your lesson.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: I'm a slow learner.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Anakin!
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Master Yoda. You have interfered with our affairs for the last time.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Count Dooku. Powerful you have become, Dooku. The dark side I sense in you.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: I've become more powerful than any Jedi. Even you.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Much to learn you still have.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: It is obvious that this contest cannot be decided by our knowledge of the Force but by our skills with a lightsaber.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: Fought well you have, my old Padawan.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: This is just the beginning.
where: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY

text: The Force is with us, my Master.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAY

text: Welcome home, Lord Tyranus. You have done well.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAY

text: I bring you good news, my Lord. The war has begun.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAY

text: Excellent. Everything is going as planned.
where: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAY

text: Do you believe what Count Dooku said about Sidious controlling the senate?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: It doesn't feel right.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: Joined the dark side Dooku has. Lies, deceit creating mistrust are his ways now.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: Nevertheless, I feel we should keep a closer eye on the senate.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: I agree.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: Where is your apprentice?
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: On his way back to Naboo. He is escorting Senator PADME home. I must admit without the clones, it would not have been a victory.
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET

text: Victory? Victory, you say? Not victory, a defeat, it was Master Obi-Wan. The shroud of the dark side has fallen. Begun, the Clone War has!
where: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
